CCD-207 PATTERN - MHz
=====================
2 phase device with I1=I2, I3=I4, S1=S2, S3=S4
Full IMO pattern.
Important for horz clks to have 90% overlap, if not done in pattern then in verniers.
PDT is used to generate delay for better hole transport in BIs (set to min for FI).
VS-st and VS-all are the same (non-FT).
Turning off horz clocks during exposure at higher speeds to
stop 'background dark signal' and 'glow'. (need to clean Hreg before readout)

High voltage rise and fall pulses need to be >25ns ( i.e. > 1*40MHz clk cycle)
27/04/2006 - Amp restore added to verticals to stop pre-amp damage.
